1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,568
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:03,070
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,805 --> 00:00:06,006
Welcome, everyone.

4
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:08,575
Hey, Seong Jun, remember my mother?

5
00:00:09,338 --> 00:00:11,278
Hello, I'm Cho Seong Jun.

6
00:00:11,278 --> 00:00:13,313
Yes, welcome.

7
00:00:14,047 --> 00:00:15,048
Ma'am.

8
00:00:16,505 --> 00:00:17,538
What?

9
00:00:18,905 --> 00:00:21,405
Look who's here!

10
00:00:22,505 --> 00:00:24,305
We met in front of the hospital
last time...

11
00:00:24,705 --> 00:00:26,638
Yes, that's right. How is this possible?

12
00:00:26,905 --> 00:00:28,005
My goodness.

13
00:00:30,038 --> 00:00:32,666
Do you know her, Yeong Hwa?

14
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:35,437
Yes, we briefly met at the hospital...

15
00:00:35,438 --> 00:00:38,105
when you were admitted last time.

16
00:00:38,338 --> 00:00:40,838
How is it that...

17
00:00:40,838 --> 00:00:43,338
everyone here somehow knows each other?

18
00:00:53,018 --> 00:00:55,555
Does he think I wore that dress
to impress him?

19
00:00:57,105 --> 00:01:00,194
Now this is how clothes should fit.
Perfect on me.

20
00:01:08,035 --> 00:01:10,671
What are you doing?
I thought you were going to work.

21
00:01:11,338 --> 00:01:13,805
Come to think of it,
I don't really need to go in today.

22
00:01:15,405 --> 00:01:17,238
But what's with the sudden cleaning?

23
00:01:18,105 --> 00:01:20,805
Didn't I tell you?
Cleaning is my favorite hobby.

24
00:01:21,114 --> 00:01:23,805
That's quite a refined hobby you've got.

25
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:26,438
Your mother must be having a hard time
on her own.

26
00:01:26,438 --> 00:01:29,289
From what I can see, her daughters
don't seem very interested in cleaning.

27
00:01:29,705 --> 00:01:32,705
What? Are you indirectly calling me messy?

28
00:01:32,705 --> 00:01:34,227
- Move.
- What?

29
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:38,305
It's your day off.
Don't you have any plans?

30
00:01:38,505 --> 00:01:41,005
Go out and have fun.
I'll do a full house cleaning.

31
00:01:41,438 --> 00:01:44,305
What?
A tenant cleaning the landlord's house?

32
00:01:44,671 --> 00:01:47,307
Look at this dust. Where's the rag?

33
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:51,505
Is he saying our house is dirty?

34
00:01:52,305 --> 00:01:53,405
It's perfectly clean.

35
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:57,084
All right. The second floor is all done,
including the bathroom.

36
00:01:57,505 --> 00:01:58,605
Did you vacuum everywhere?

37
00:01:58,605 --> 00:01:59,605
Yes, it's all done.

38
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:03,791
You two look just like newlyweds.

39
00:02:04,038 --> 00:02:05,038
You two.

40
00:02:06,538 --> 00:02:08,395
All right, start the briefing.

41
00:02:08,638 --> 00:02:11,899
Leave nothing out. I want every detail.

42
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,905
So you two slept in the same bed?

43
00:02:19,638 --> 00:02:21,905
That day,
the mala bindaetteok was too spicy,

44
00:02:21,905 --> 00:02:23,605
so I drank too quickly
on an empty stomach.

45
00:02:24,005 --> 00:02:27,214
Plus, that room used to be mine
until recently, so...

46
00:02:27,781 --> 00:02:28,784
My goodness.

47
00:02:29,005 --> 00:02:31,305
Hey, did you actually pounce on him
just because I told you to?

48
00:02:31,805 --> 00:02:33,053
What? Pounce?

49
00:02:34,105 --> 00:02:35,622
No, it's not that...

50
00:02:35,622 --> 00:02:38,425
Then was that night
your first night together?

51
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,105
What do you mean by "first night?"

52
00:02:41,038 --> 00:02:43,163
No, that would be the second night.

53
00:02:43,505 --> 00:02:45,938
Don't you remember the night
we worked late and slept together.

54
00:02:45,938 --> 00:02:47,205
That was the first night.

55
00:02:47,605 --> 00:02:48,605
Team Manager.

56
00:02:48,805 --> 00:02:49,805
What in the world?

57
00:02:49,805 --> 00:02:52,639
Hey, you went that far without telling me?

58
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:55,305
Why is your choice of words so weird?

59
00:02:56,105 --> 00:02:58,105
Cho Rong,
don't get any strange ideas, okay?

60
00:02:58,105 --> 00:03:00,005
All this talk about a "first night"
and "sleeping together"...

61
00:03:00,005 --> 00:03:01,905
Don't let your imagination run wild.

62
00:03:02,138 --> 00:03:03,483
Don't go there, okay?

63
00:03:04,251 --> 00:03:06,051
Go where?

64
00:03:07,224 --> 00:03:09,756
I keep imagining things!

65
00:03:10,005 --> 00:03:11,505
Hey, that's enough. You should go.

66
00:03:11,505 --> 00:03:12,559
Get up, hurry.

67
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:15,929
I have more.
Should I continue the briefing?

68
00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:17,798
Seriously...

69
00:03:17,938 --> 00:03:19,738
No, let's stop here for today.

70
00:03:19,738 --> 00:03:21,935
It'd be a waste
to hear all the fun stuff at once.

71
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:24,105
I need to get ready for business,
so I'll go.

72
00:03:24,105 --> 00:03:26,340
You two carry on with what you were doing.

73
00:03:26,538 --> 00:03:28,909
Hey, don't you dare
say anything weird to Grandma.

74
00:03:31,478 --> 00:03:33,538
Move, I need to clean.

75
00:03:36,605 --> 00:03:38,719
Thank you for inviting us.

76
00:03:39,338 --> 00:03:40,605
No need to thank us.

77
00:03:40,605 --> 00:03:45,238
You two high school friends
are working so hard under our family,

78
00:03:45,705 --> 00:03:48,729
so it's only right
we treat our subordinates this much.

79
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:51,838
Crystal, what do you mean?

80
00:03:51,838 --> 00:03:55,038
Today, we're clearly gathered as friends.

81
00:03:55,505 --> 00:03:57,404
Right, Seong Jun? Gwon Sik?

82
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:03,276
Yeah, that's right.

83
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,580
Your mother prepared all this food,

84
00:04:08,305 --> 00:04:10,417
but she won't be eating with us.
I feel bad.

85
00:04:10,538 --> 00:04:11,652
No, it's fine.

86
00:04:12,305 --> 00:04:14,621
They can enjoy a quiet meal out together,

87
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:17,038
like a date. It's perfectly fine.

88
00:04:17,205 --> 00:04:20,205
My husband felt so sorry...

89
00:04:20,205 --> 00:04:22,805
that his top student friend
ended up working as a janitor.

90
00:04:23,605 --> 00:04:25,805
So I felt bad too, and said,

91
00:04:25,805 --> 00:04:29,069
"Why not bring him in as your assistant?
That's what friends are for.

92
00:04:29,571 --> 00:04:33,240
People like us
should practice oblisse noblege."

93
00:04:35,490 --> 00:04:38,157
Crystal, it's "noblesse oblige."

94
00:04:38,905 --> 00:04:41,014
Yes, noblesse noblige.

95
00:04:43,405 --> 00:04:44,905
Please focus on me.

96
00:04:45,205 --> 00:04:47,338
Allow me to introduce this champagne.

97
00:04:47,338 --> 00:04:49,105
You've probably all heard of it.

98
00:04:49,338 --> 00:04:53,160
It's a La Maison d'Or vintage
imported directly from France.

99
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,005
That's enough.

100
00:04:55,205 --> 00:04:56,305
Let's just open it, okay?

101
00:04:56,305 --> 00:04:57,305
- Shall we?
- Yes.

102
00:04:57,305 --> 00:04:58,505
Don't shake it! Stop!

103
00:04:59,105 --> 00:05:00,905
It'll foam. It's expensive.

104
00:05:00,905 --> 00:05:02,405
- Don't shake it.
- Why not?

105
00:05:02,405 --> 00:05:04,538
Champagne is all about the bubbles.

106
00:05:04,738 --> 00:05:06,705
Take this off first. Yes, that's it.

107
00:05:10,876 --> 00:05:11,876
Honey! What do I do?

108
00:05:11,876 --> 00:05:12,896
- Help me.
- I told you!

109
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:15,405
I told you not to shake it!

110
00:05:15,405 --> 00:05:16,405
I'm just going to...

111
00:05:16,405 --> 00:05:17,751
What should I do?

112
00:05:18,638 --> 00:05:19,705
Why does it keep overflowing?

113
00:05:20,005 --> 00:05:21,905
Look at your forehead.

114
00:05:23,605 --> 00:05:24,605
Am I bleeding?

115
00:05:24,605 --> 00:05:26,293
There's no blood. Does it hurt?

116
00:05:26,505 --> 00:05:28,238
- It doesn't hurt.
- My goodness.

117
00:05:28,238 --> 00:05:29,463
But what a waste.

118
00:05:32,505 --> 00:05:33,505
What do we do?

119
00:05:33,938 --> 00:05:36,805
- It hurts, seriously.
- You'll see this kind of thing often.

120
00:05:39,553 --> 00:05:41,808
This is so upsetting.

121
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:45,905
So you met Mr. Cho's wife at the hospital?

122
00:05:46,205 --> 00:05:49,650
Yes, when you were admitted last time.

123
00:05:49,983 --> 00:05:51,218
After meeting Dr. Kim,

124
00:05:51,218 --> 00:05:53,738
I was upset and sitting on a bench,

125
00:05:54,338 --> 00:05:57,324
and she was crying about her daughter.

126
00:05:58,505 --> 00:05:59,705
Her daughter, a med student,

127
00:05:59,705 --> 00:06:02,829
had apparently dropped out
without telling her.

128
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,604
It was so heartbreaking...

129
00:06:06,184 --> 00:06:10,270
that I spoke to her without thinking,
hoping to comfort her.

130
00:06:11,638 --> 00:06:14,574
If it was you, I'm sure it helped.

131
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:17,077
I was the one who was comforted.

132
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:21,305
She offered to share the lunchbox...

133
00:06:21,305 --> 00:06:22,905
she had carefully prepared
for her daughter.

134
00:06:24,305 --> 00:06:25,986
That beef bone soup she gave me...

135
00:06:27,038 --> 00:06:29,205
was so rich and warm,

136
00:06:29,438 --> 00:06:31,825
it comforted my heart.

137
00:06:32,505 --> 00:06:34,428
To think someone you met like that...

138
00:06:34,905 --> 00:06:37,105
became part of Kangsu Construction.

139
00:06:37,905 --> 00:06:39,599
What a deep connection.

140
00:06:41,705 --> 00:06:43,036
That's not all.

141
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:46,139
The woman who helped me...

142
00:06:46,139 --> 00:06:47,738
when I collapsed on the street...

143
00:06:48,205 --> 00:06:51,005
The one who developed Joy.

144
00:06:51,705 --> 00:06:53,505
She is Mr. Cho's daughter.

145
00:06:53,505 --> 00:06:54,581
Really?

146
00:06:55,816 --> 00:06:58,084
That's quite a connection.

147
00:06:58,805 --> 00:07:01,905
I was actually thinking of meeting
that developer.

148
00:07:01,905 --> 00:07:03,905
You should.

149
00:07:04,557 --> 00:07:06,960
She seems like a good teammate
for Gyeol too.

150
00:07:09,005 --> 00:07:10,905
I look fine, right? Shall we go?

151
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:12,331
Let's go.

152
00:07:15,001 --> 00:07:17,304
(Kangsu Construction)

153
00:07:19,937 --> 00:07:20,937
Got you.

154
00:07:21,605 --> 00:07:23,005
I knew you'd be here.

155
00:07:23,505 --> 00:07:25,005
What brings you to the office
on a day off?

156
00:07:25,624 --> 00:07:28,448
Weren't you going
to the Team Manager's housewarming?

157
00:07:28,905 --> 00:07:32,238
What fun is a housewarming alone?
Not that I was invited.

158
00:07:35,905 --> 00:07:37,805
Should we actually organize one?

159
00:07:38,297 --> 00:07:40,119
If you go, I'm in.

160
00:07:41,244 --> 00:07:44,097
I'm busy with the retirement community
sports facility report.

161
00:07:44,305 --> 00:07:45,732
You can take your time with that.

162
00:07:46,605 --> 00:07:49,569
I'll turn on the speaker. Help me out.

163
00:07:53,305 --> 00:07:54,305
Hey, Team Manager Ko.

164
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:57,430
How's your new place? Do you like it?

165
00:07:58,604 --> 00:08:00,780
It's fine. What's up?

166
00:08:01,038 --> 00:08:03,083
I'm here with Manager Seo.

167
00:08:03,705 --> 00:08:06,219
If it's near the office,
we thought we'd check it out...

168
00:08:06,219 --> 00:08:08,438
and grab lunch, housewarming and all.

169
00:08:08,438 --> 00:08:10,605
What housewarming?

170
00:08:12,338 --> 00:08:14,528
Team Manager, I finished cleaning.

171
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:21,001
What was that voice just now?
Don't tell me Ms. Cho...

172
00:08:24,987 --> 00:08:25,988
Weren't you alone?

173
00:08:25,988 --> 00:08:29,005
What are you saying? The place
is so small there's nowhere to sit.

174
00:08:29,005 --> 00:08:31,005
I'll treat you to a meal later.
I'm hanging up.

175
00:08:33,264 --> 00:08:34,264
What was that call?

176
00:08:35,058 --> 00:08:37,884
Was it Chief Ko? Is he coming here?

177
00:08:38,151 --> 00:08:40,738
I told him no to the housewarming.

178
00:08:40,738 --> 00:08:43,038
What? See?

179
00:08:43,038 --> 00:08:45,005
I knew something like this would happen.

180
00:08:45,591 --> 00:08:47,794
This won't do.
You need to find another place fast.

181
00:08:48,905 --> 00:08:50,931
All right, the cleaning is done.

182
00:08:52,137 --> 00:08:55,969
Why don't you actually listen
when people talk to you?

183
00:08:56,905 --> 00:08:58,138
Right, you have something to do.

184
00:08:58,138 --> 00:08:59,905
What? What now?

185
00:08:59,905 --> 00:09:02,042
Go upstairs and stay there for 30 minutes.

186
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:03,938
You're talking so much,
it's making my ears hurt.

187
00:09:03,938 --> 00:09:06,205
- Here, take this.
- This is my house, you know?

188
00:09:06,205 --> 00:09:07,881
Team Manager's orders. Go.

189
00:09:08,838 --> 00:09:11,785
Then I'll finish up the master bedroom
while I'm at it.

190
00:09:12,005 --> 00:09:13,005
Okay.

191
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:18,058
He said the place is too small to sit.

192
00:09:18,984 --> 00:09:21,194
But I guess there's room
for Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

193
00:09:23,538 --> 00:09:25,205
I'm sorry, I shouldn't have called...

194
00:09:25,444 --> 00:09:26,444
It's fine.

195
00:09:27,424 --> 00:09:30,537
I expected this
when he said he was moving out.

196
00:09:32,206 --> 00:09:33,206
Are you really okay?

197
00:09:34,476 --> 00:09:36,276
Are you okay, saying that to me?

198
00:09:37,918 --> 00:09:41,781
In a way, we're like...

199
00:09:42,625 --> 00:09:44,951
mirrors to each other, don't you think?

200
00:09:45,864 --> 00:09:47,764
A mirror I'd rather not look into.

201
00:09:50,105 --> 00:09:52,805
Since I'm here anyway,
I might as well do some work.

202
00:09:54,038 --> 00:09:56,005
Send me the report when it's done.

203
00:10:11,405 --> 00:10:12,579
Welcome.

204
00:10:15,338 --> 00:10:17,905
- Sit over here.
- It's been a while.

205
00:10:19,586 --> 00:10:25,625
You two look so lovely together.

206
00:10:29,205 --> 00:10:32,138
Thank you, but one more person is coming.

207
00:10:32,138 --> 00:10:33,438
Is that so?

208
00:10:33,438 --> 00:10:36,538
Will you order the same as last time?

209
00:10:36,538 --> 00:10:38,171
Yes, the original set, please.

210
00:10:38,171 --> 00:10:39,605
- Yes.
- We...

211
00:10:39,605 --> 00:10:41,641
also have three new menu items.

212
00:10:42,005 --> 00:10:44,005
Do you want to lose regulars?

213
00:10:46,005 --> 00:10:47,638
She's my granddaughter.

214
00:10:47,638 --> 00:10:50,805
She keeps trying to attract
younger customers with nonsense.

215
00:10:51,105 --> 00:10:53,705
We'll order the original first
and order more if needed.

216
00:10:54,305 --> 00:10:55,438
Yes, thank you.

217
00:10:57,305 --> 00:10:59,025
- Welcome.
- Yes.

218
00:11:03,337 --> 00:11:05,431
What is it? Why are you staring?

219
00:11:06,584 --> 00:11:09,001
Sorry? It's nothing.

220
00:11:10,305 --> 00:11:13,105
You just look familiar.

221
00:11:13,105 --> 00:11:17,344
Really? I've never seen you before.

222
00:11:19,505 --> 00:11:21,481
You look very familiar though.

223
00:11:26,405 --> 00:11:29,305
What's wrong?
You're making the owner uncomfortable.

224
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,659
I apologize. Anyway,

225
00:11:33,905 --> 00:11:36,705
is this a regular place for you, Chairman?

226
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:41,505
Chairman? Is he the chairman
of some senior association?

227
00:11:43,705 --> 00:11:45,505
What kind of bindaetteok do they have?

228
00:11:49,505 --> 00:11:51,911
Did that man eat something weird?

229
00:11:51,911 --> 00:11:53,046
Why is he acting like that?

230
00:11:58,111 --> 00:11:59,919
It's been 30 minutes, Team Manager.

231
00:12:01,538 --> 00:12:02,956
What's that smell?

232
00:12:02,956 --> 00:12:04,838
It's almost done. Just wait a moment.

233
00:12:21,905 --> 00:12:22,905
Alright, sit.

234
00:12:23,205 --> 00:12:24,878
What? Okay.

235
00:12:37,305 --> 00:12:40,205
I'll show you first.

236
00:12:40,705 --> 00:12:42,738
Show me? Show me what?

237
00:12:43,505 --> 00:12:45,605
You hold it like this,

238
00:12:46,805 --> 00:12:49,605
and then get it out in one go.

239
00:12:52,205 --> 00:12:53,605
Normally you'd use clams,

240
00:12:53,605 --> 00:12:55,405
but there were some sea snails
in the fridge.

241
00:12:56,405 --> 00:12:59,679
I thought you just boil them
and pick them out with a toothpick.

242
00:13:10,005 --> 00:13:12,538
Are you sure you weren't a chef before,
not an architect?

243
00:13:13,205 --> 00:13:14,927
Is there anything you can't do,
Team Manager?

244
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:19,005
Well,
I've been looking for about 30 years,

245
00:13:19,005 --> 00:13:20,305
but there's nothing I can't do yet.

246
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,403
What a showoff.

247
00:13:24,605 --> 00:13:27,305
Eat up. You'll need your strength later.

248
00:13:27,805 --> 00:13:29,838
What? We still have work to do?

249
00:13:31,257 --> 00:13:33,946
This is the medical chopper
transporting an emergency patient.

250
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:36,549
- Secure the airway!
- Seriously?

251
00:13:37,205 --> 00:13:38,348
Prepare the Ambu bag.

252
00:13:43,238 --> 00:13:45,124
Hey, can't you do anything right?

253
00:13:46,857 --> 00:13:49,429
You call yourself an intern and you can't
even squeeze an Ambu bag properly?

254
00:13:49,838 --> 00:13:50,971
Do you have a death wish?

255
00:13:53,438 --> 00:13:55,635
What are you doing?
Why are you standing there?

256
00:13:57,738 --> 00:14:00,305
Bravo.

257
00:14:00,305 --> 00:14:03,610
You're quite loud, aren't you?
I'm talking about your working style.

258
00:14:05,277 --> 00:14:08,905
When I get immersed,
I feel like I'm on-site,

259
00:14:08,905 --> 00:14:11,317
so I've gotten used to speaking out loud
while writing.

260
00:14:11,805 --> 00:14:14,854
I get it, but this is a shared space...

261
00:14:17,931 --> 00:14:20,293
Hey, Hye Ji. You're already here?

262
00:14:20,638 --> 00:14:21,761
Come in.

263
00:14:22,638 --> 00:14:25,838
Ms. Cho, didn't you say...

264
00:14:25,838 --> 00:14:27,533
absolutely no outsiders allowed?

265
00:14:28,505 --> 00:14:32,405
So you're saying I should tell my friend,
who just arrived, not to come in?

266
00:14:32,405 --> 00:14:33,405
No...

267
00:14:37,511 --> 00:14:39,679
- Eun Nim.
- Hye Ji.

268
00:14:43,638 --> 00:14:45,618
Keep it short.

269
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:46,958
Who is this?

270
00:14:52,038 --> 00:14:54,594
I'm webtoon artist Seo Seung Wu.

271
00:14:55,844 --> 00:14:57,597
You're the one she's collaborating with?

272
00:14:58,605 --> 00:14:59,705
Hello.

273
00:15:00,005 --> 00:15:03,469
I'm Oh Hye Ji, Eun Nim's college friend.

274
00:15:04,705 --> 00:15:05,905
Then I hope you have a good time.

275
00:15:08,605 --> 00:15:09,605
Sit down.

276
00:15:11,638 --> 00:15:13,105
You're busy these days, right?

277
00:15:13,105 --> 00:15:16,282
Busy? I've practically given up
on living like a human.

278
00:15:17,205 --> 00:15:18,605
You look good, though.

279
00:15:18,605 --> 00:15:22,088
It makes me regret
not dropping out sooner.

280
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:29,128
What is it? If you're uncomfortable,
should I ask him to step out?

281
00:15:29,128 --> 00:15:31,697
Hey! No, it's not that...

282
00:15:32,605 --> 00:15:34,705
He's totally my type.

283
00:15:34,705 --> 00:15:35,902
What? Your type?

284
00:15:37,838 --> 00:15:39,839
His looks are insane.

285
00:15:39,991 --> 00:15:42,041
Your eyes are insane.

286
00:15:42,405 --> 00:15:43,605
What "looks?"

287
00:15:51,138 --> 00:15:54,854
As you all know,
I majored in French literature.

288
00:15:55,805 --> 00:15:59,459
So I'm quite knowledgeable
about French cuisine and culture.

289
00:16:00,605 --> 00:16:03,930
This here is called mille-feuille.

290
00:16:04,430 --> 00:16:06,799
It means "a thousand layers."

291
00:16:07,505 --> 00:16:09,305
It's a French dessert...

292
00:16:09,805 --> 00:16:12,705
made by layering various fillings...

293
00:16:12,964 --> 00:16:14,440
between thin pastry sheets.

294
00:16:15,205 --> 00:16:17,105
Really? So we can eat it now, right?

295
00:16:17,105 --> 00:16:19,463
Wait, there's a bit more.

296
00:16:20,905 --> 00:16:24,409
Mille-feuille is also called Napoleon.

297
00:16:26,384 --> 00:16:30,289
Apparently, Napoleon liked it so much
that it got that name.

298
00:16:35,305 --> 00:16:36,605
What does that smile mean?

299
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:39,632
It's nothing.

300
00:16:40,738 --> 00:16:42,902
Now,
you cut the mille-feuille like this...

301
00:16:43,478 --> 00:16:46,105
Wait, if you cut it like that,

302
00:16:46,105 --> 00:16:48,307
the cream gets pushed out
and it falls apart easily.

303
00:16:48,544 --> 00:16:50,743
You should lay it down like this.

304
00:16:52,238 --> 00:16:55,818
And it's not because Napoleon liked it.

305
00:16:55,818 --> 00:16:58,918
It's called Napolitain, from Naples...

306
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:13,699
Thank you, Min Ho's mom.

307
00:17:14,605 --> 00:17:15,605
Min Ho's mom?

308
00:17:16,305 --> 00:17:19,472
Now that you know who I am,
let's clarify how you address me.

309
00:17:21,005 --> 00:17:22,005
Excuse me?

310
00:17:23,005 --> 00:17:26,005
Mr. Cho,
even though this is a private setting,

311
00:17:26,005 --> 00:17:27,747
we should be clear about hierarchy.

312
00:17:28,538 --> 00:17:31,205
Make sure your wife understands that too.

313
00:17:32,738 --> 00:17:34,053
Yes, sir.

314
00:17:37,438 --> 00:17:40,093
My apologies, madam.

315
00:17:45,338 --> 00:17:46,338
Hello?

316
00:17:47,705 --> 00:17:49,869
What? You found her?

317
00:17:52,538 --> 00:17:53,639
Yes.

318
00:17:54,205 --> 00:17:55,205
What do we do, honey?

319
00:17:55,518 --> 00:17:57,510
You found what?

320
00:17:59,605 --> 00:18:00,605
Mother's daughter.

321
00:18:02,105 --> 00:18:03,105
What?

322
00:18:04,638 --> 00:18:05,818
What's wrong, sir?

323
00:18:06,038 --> 00:18:07,954
No, it's nothing.

324
00:18:07,954 --> 00:18:09,422
Wait a moment.

325
00:18:11,238 --> 00:18:13,905
What's going on? Found what?

326
00:18:13,905 --> 00:18:16,605
There's just this thing
that should never be found.

327
00:18:21,105 --> 00:18:23,405
Yes, Chairman. You've already arrived?

328
00:18:24,136 --> 00:18:26,204
Yes, I'll be waiting.

329
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:29,442
What? What did you find?

330
00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:32,178
You'll hear it directly
from the Chairman later.

331
00:18:32,579 --> 00:18:33,579
Seo Gwon Sik.

332
00:18:34,082 --> 00:18:36,215
Did you forget
this is a gathering with family?

333
00:18:36,638 --> 00:18:38,351
Then just tell me.

334
00:18:40,038 --> 00:18:41,320
Are you sure? Is it Mother's daughter?

335
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:46,738
Sir, it seems something has come up,
so we'll take our leave.

336
00:18:46,738 --> 00:18:48,194
Yes, that's probably best.

337
00:18:48,405 --> 00:18:50,930
Don't forget to come to the house
early Monday morning.

338
00:18:51,105 --> 00:18:52,105
Yes.

339
00:18:53,005 --> 00:18:54,467
Thank you for the invitation.

340
00:18:54,938 --> 00:18:55,938
Yes.

341
00:18:57,805 --> 00:19:00,305
Father, why did you come back so early?

342
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:02,308
The Chairman was feeling tired.

343
00:19:02,538 --> 00:19:04,544
Chairman, we'll take our leave.

344
00:19:04,544 --> 00:19:07,013
All right, take care. Come inside.

345
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:10,049
Thank you for the meal, ma'am.

346
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:13,252
Yes, get home safe.

347
00:19:13,638 --> 00:19:14,805
I won't see you out.

348
00:19:14,805 --> 00:19:18,324
Why are you going in there
when they didn't even call for you?

349
00:19:18,958 --> 00:19:21,138
It's our family matter.
I need to know. Move.

350
00:19:21,138 --> 00:19:22,562
- Wait.
- What's wrong with you?

351
00:19:23,051 --> 00:19:24,696
We'll be going now.

352
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:26,298
- Bye.
- Bye.

353
00:19:29,918 --> 00:19:32,571
The adoption and relinquishment records
match the same period,

354
00:19:32,938 --> 00:19:34,273
and the age range is similar.

355
00:19:35,005 --> 00:19:37,276
So when can I meet her?

356
00:19:37,505 --> 00:19:39,245
I've scheduled a meeting
for the day after tomorrow.

357
00:19:39,905 --> 00:19:42,314
We'll also proceed with a DNA test then.

358
00:19:52,292 --> 00:19:53,292
What are you doing?

359
00:19:53,938 --> 00:19:56,796
Father, we should know too.
Who did you find?

360
00:19:57,705 --> 00:20:00,138
How can we be the only ones
left in the dark?

361
00:20:00,438 --> 00:20:03,302
Get out.
I'll tell you when the time comes.

362
00:20:03,605 --> 00:20:06,038
Father, that's too much.

363
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:07,473
Get out now.

364
00:20:09,031 --> 00:20:10,909
Yes, understood.

365
00:20:11,557 --> 00:20:13,045
Honey, where are you going?

366
00:20:13,305 --> 00:20:14,605
He told us to leave.

367
00:20:22,011 --> 00:20:24,390
What time and where should we go
the day after tomorrow?

368
00:20:24,905 --> 00:20:26,125
Are you going too, Madam?

369
00:20:26,964 --> 00:20:29,495
Yeong Hwa, wait at home.

370
00:20:29,838 --> 00:20:31,205
I'll go first.

371
00:20:32,138 --> 00:20:36,335
Come once the DNA test confirms it.

372
00:20:36,744 --> 00:20:39,677
No, I can't wait until then.

373
00:20:40,938 --> 00:20:42,305
If it's really Yeon Sun,

374
00:20:43,805 --> 00:20:46,112
I'll know the moment I see her.

375
00:20:50,005 --> 00:20:52,051
Dad, I'm ready for our walk.

376
00:20:52,605 --> 00:20:54,286
I'm ready too. Shall we go?

377
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:58,124
Can Mom come with us?

378
00:20:58,638 --> 00:21:01,193
Mom too? Should we ask her?

379
00:21:01,193 --> 00:21:02,728
(ALPHA AI Global Algorithm Fund)

380
00:21:05,305 --> 00:21:06,599
I put in 2,000 dollars,

381
00:21:07,538 --> 00:21:09,735
and it's already up to 2,400 dollars
in just a few days?

382
00:21:12,338 --> 00:21:14,073
Is there any way
I can get a lump sum of money?

383
00:21:17,538 --> 00:21:21,347
Mom, we're going for a walk in the park.
Want to come?

384
00:21:22,038 --> 00:21:23,215
A walk?

385
00:21:24,238 --> 00:21:26,953
I'd rather stay home and rest.

386
00:21:27,605 --> 00:21:29,221
You two go ahead.

387
00:21:29,458 --> 00:21:32,158
Honey, you're not sick, are you?

388
00:21:32,805 --> 00:21:35,194
You haven't been sleeping well lately.

389
00:21:35,705 --> 00:21:37,496
No, I'm fine.

390
00:21:38,738 --> 00:21:40,338
- Go on.
- Okay.

391
00:21:44,905 --> 00:21:46,372
Hello, sir. Yes.

392
00:21:49,038 --> 00:21:51,243
You want 20,000 dollars more
for the deposit?

393
00:21:52,005 --> 00:21:53,746
But sir, we... Hello?

394
00:21:56,438 --> 00:21:59,785
What? He wants to raise the deposit
by 20,000 dollars?

395
00:22:00,153 --> 00:22:01,153
What do we do?

396
00:22:02,178 --> 00:22:04,990
How are we supposed to come up
with that much money all of a sudden?

397
00:22:05,877 --> 00:22:07,637
We have no choice. We have to move.

398
00:22:08,084 --> 00:22:09,984
I'll ask my mother
to find a cheaper place.

399
00:22:11,338 --> 00:22:13,338
Where would that be?

400
00:22:13,338 --> 00:22:16,105
Honey, there's always another way.

401
00:22:16,543 --> 00:22:18,010
Don't worry too much, okay?

402
00:22:18,538 --> 00:22:20,005
Bit Na, let's go.

403
00:22:20,505 --> 00:22:22,008
I'll be back, Mom.

404
00:22:22,405 --> 00:22:24,143
- Okay, have a good time.
- See you.

405
00:22:28,605 --> 00:22:31,384
The deposit is already 50,000 dollars,
and he wants...

406
00:22:36,038 --> 00:22:37,490
There's a way!

407
00:22:43,105 --> 00:22:45,898
Hello, you just called my husband.

408
00:22:46,605 --> 00:22:50,136
Yes, about the deposit...

409
00:22:56,605 --> 00:22:59,545
I told you to take a nap.
You didn't sleep?

410
00:23:00,605 --> 00:23:02,905
I lay down, but I couldn't fall asleep.

411
00:23:02,905 --> 00:23:03,905
Come sit down.

412
00:23:09,005 --> 00:23:11,805
Do you remember how many times...

413
00:23:11,938 --> 00:23:15,005
we've been through this over the years?

414
00:23:16,105 --> 00:23:17,705
We thought we'd found her, but we hadn't.

415
00:23:18,305 --> 00:23:20,766
Then we again thought we found her,
but we still hadn't.

416
00:23:21,191 --> 00:23:23,402
Yes, countless times.

417
00:23:25,138 --> 00:23:28,405
There's no guarantee
that won't happen again, so...

418
00:23:29,690 --> 00:23:33,078
No, it feels different this time.

419
00:23:34,738 --> 00:23:36,838
I really think we'll find her this time.

420
00:23:37,149 --> 00:23:39,251
I wish that were true.

421
00:23:40,185 --> 00:23:43,622
Still, let's not get our hopes up
too high...

422
00:23:44,438 --> 00:23:46,292
and just wait calmly.

423
00:23:47,138 --> 00:23:49,895
Yes, I understand.

424
00:23:50,705 --> 00:23:53,438
I'll calm down and wait.

425
00:23:57,838 --> 00:23:59,238
So what do we do now?

426
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:02,538
If it's really her, what happens next?

427
00:24:02,905 --> 00:24:05,805
What do you mean?
I'll get a sister I never had.

428
00:24:06,105 --> 00:24:08,481
Wait, would she be an older sister?

429
00:24:08,738 --> 00:24:12,351
You know what will happen
if Father registers her, right?

430
00:24:15,691 --> 00:24:18,391
If you get half,
then Min Ho gets half of that.

431
00:24:18,938 --> 00:24:22,094
No, with Gyeol,
doesn't it become a fraction of that?

432
00:24:23,232 --> 00:24:26,332
No way. We can't just let that happen.

433
00:24:26,938 --> 00:24:28,867
What else can we do?

434
00:24:30,438 --> 00:24:33,973
Right, a lawsuit. Let's file a lawsuit.

435
00:24:34,538 --> 00:24:36,375
A lawsuit? On what grounds?

436
00:24:36,771 --> 00:24:39,605
She's not even related by blood to Father,

437
00:24:39,605 --> 00:24:41,305
and just because she's Mother's daughter,

438
00:24:41,305 --> 00:24:43,916
she gets half our assets?
That's ridiculous.

439
00:24:44,438 --> 00:24:47,152
It's like being robbed in broad daylight.

440
00:24:48,005 --> 00:24:49,355
Robbed?

441
00:24:49,705 --> 00:24:52,591
That hurts just thinking about it.

442
00:24:52,738 --> 00:24:55,205
Let's meet a lawyer first...

443
00:24:55,505 --> 00:24:57,105
and figure out a legal strategy.

444
00:24:57,805 --> 00:24:59,005
Call Lawyer Kang.

445
00:25:00,038 --> 00:25:03,202
He's Father's man. Why would we call him?

446
00:25:03,202 --> 00:25:05,805
Then find another law firm.

447
00:25:05,805 --> 00:25:07,606
The biggest one in the country.

448
00:25:08,505 --> 00:25:09,505
Eun Su Jeong.

449
00:25:10,538 --> 00:25:13,505
This situation really upsets me.

450
00:25:14,138 --> 00:25:17,416
After finding her,
he still keeps it a secret from me?

451
00:25:18,138 --> 00:25:20,052
How could he do that when I'm his child?

452
00:25:20,338 --> 00:25:23,689
Father aside,
I'm more upset with Jeong Ran.

453
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:26,225
We see each other almost every day,

454
00:25:26,405 --> 00:25:28,705
and she never once hinted at it.

455
00:25:34,956 --> 00:25:38,205
How could you do this to me?

456
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:40,172
What?

457
00:25:40,305 --> 00:25:43,409
Who did you find? Who is it?

458
00:25:44,138 --> 00:25:45,311
Tell me.

459
00:25:50,405 --> 00:25:51,450
Yes, Su Jeong.

460
00:25:51,450 --> 00:25:53,952
Aren't you going too far?

461
00:25:54,987 --> 00:25:57,756
How could you act like
you knew nothing this whole time?

462
00:25:58,138 --> 00:25:59,625
What do you mean, act like I knew nothing?

463
00:26:01,338 --> 00:26:03,362
You're denying it to the very end?

464
00:26:03,905 --> 00:26:07,866
You didn't know Gwon Sik was looking
for Mother's daughter?

465
00:26:08,805 --> 00:26:11,338
What? What are you talking about?

466
00:26:12,705 --> 00:26:16,205
Madam had a daughter?

467
00:26:19,205 --> 00:26:20,805
You really didn't know?

468
00:26:21,905 --> 00:26:25,818
Unbelievable.
No matter how tight-lipped he is...

469
00:26:26,805 --> 00:26:28,754
Are you two even a real couple?

470
00:26:29,038 --> 00:26:30,605
What did you just say?

471
00:26:32,105 --> 00:26:33,105
I'm hanging up.

472
00:26:39,565 --> 00:26:42,835
How can a couple
keep something like that a secret?

473
00:26:45,505 --> 00:26:47,573
Why are you looking at me?

474
00:26:48,405 --> 00:26:50,409
I have no secrets from you. I swear.

475
00:26:51,111 --> 00:26:53,812
I swear. For real, I don't.

476
00:26:54,816 --> 00:26:55,816
Really?

477
00:26:56,838 --> 00:26:59,405
So you're transparent like me?

478
00:26:59,405 --> 00:27:00,405
Honey, I love you.

479
00:27:03,605 --> 00:27:05,724
Seriously, after feeding me and all...

480
00:27:05,724 --> 00:27:07,359
Shaking blankets was the hard work
you were talking about?

481
00:27:07,359 --> 00:27:08,794
Grab the other end.

482
00:27:09,644 --> 00:27:13,505
There's this one scene in dramas
I find ridiculous.

483
00:27:13,505 --> 00:27:16,338
A man and a woman
shake a blanket together,

484
00:27:16,338 --> 00:27:19,538
and when she lets go,
she dramatically falls into his arms.

485
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:21,440
Don't you think that's ridiculous?

486
00:27:21,738 --> 00:27:24,805
Enough chatter. On three, shake it.

487
00:27:24,805 --> 00:27:27,212
One, two, three.

488
00:28:09,988 --> 00:28:12,991
(Our Happy Days)

489
00:28:13,138 --> 00:28:15,594
When are you ever going to look at me?

490
00:28:15,594 --> 00:28:18,130
Ever since I moved into this house,
I've been smiling a lot.

491
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:21,066
Is it okay for me to be this happy?

492
00:28:21,066 --> 00:28:22,801
I'm fine with being hurt,

493
00:28:22,801 --> 00:28:24,703
but I can't bear to see you hurt anymore.

494
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:26,405
Let's stop, please.

495
00:28:26,672 --> 00:28:29,107
Honey, they just left.

496
00:28:29,107 --> 00:28:31,638
What if it's really her?

497
00:28:31,910 --> 00:28:33,512
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
